-- Consolidated Contracting Gets $132 Million Contract From Abu Dhabi Ports
-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 2010-10-03T07:55:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/consolidated-contracting-gets-132-million-contract-from-abu-dhabi-ports.html
Abu Dhabi Ports Co. awarded a
contract valued at 484.6 million dirhams ($132 million) to
Consolidated Contracting Engineering & Procurement SAL for
infrastructure works at the Khalifa Port and Industrial Zone.  The agreement is for the construction, fit-out, testing and
commissioning of the civil and structural works, Abu Dhabi Ports
said in an e-mailed statement today. Construction works is
scheduled to end in July 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in Abu Dhabi at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  